        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">Literature, statistics</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">Ozone- and NO2-emission factors are based on published measurements made in various countries. Assumptions for the amount of transmission network per kWh transported and emissions per kWh are based on Swiss data. Electricity losses data are based on EMPRESA 2021 data and on data from Treyer et al. (2014) EMPRESA, D.P.E.E., 2021. Anuário Estatístico de Energia Elétrica 2021 ano base 2020. Rio de Janeiro: EPE.. Available: https://www.epe.gov.br/sites-pt/publicacoes-dados-abertos/publicacoes/PublicacoesArquivos/publicacao-160/topico-168/Anu%C3%A1rio_2021.pdf#page=1&amp;zoom=auto,-248,653 Treyer, Karin &amp; Bauer, Christian. (2014). Life cycle inventories of electricity generation and power supply in version 3 of the ecoinvent database?Part II: Electricity markets. The International Journal of Life Cycle Assessment. 21. 10.1007/s11367-013-0694-x.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
      <review reviewedMajorRelease="3" reviewedMinorRelease="0" reviewedMajorRevision="0" reviewedMinorRevision="25" reviewerId="610bd1b2-fec3-4e8e-84a6-76fef8b6b7b8" reviewerName="Karin Treyer" reviewerEmail="karin.treyer@psi.ch" reviewDate="2018-01-24">
        <details>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The loss values in this dataset need to be revised in a wholistic way over the whole market- transformation dataset chain. This will be done in an integrated way after accept of all affected datasets into the database.</text>
        </details>
      </review>
